Defines the agent-facing tool contract for `ctx-status`, a task backlog manager that reads from and writes to `docs/status.json`. The three commands are `list` (prints sorted backlog with ids), `add-task` (appends a row with auto-assigned id and regenerates `docs/STATUS.md`), and `delete-task` (removes by id and regenerates markdown). The `CONTRACT` constant is the single source of truth — the generated tool-contract block in `CLAUDE.md` and `README.md` is assembled from this string via `--contract` flag, and the `contracts` battery check fails if the docs drift from it.